Scott,

All the R packages from CRAN in the repository have an "r-cran-" prefix. 
  So the correct command would be:

sudo apt-get install r-cran-lme4

Not sure if you are using Debian or Ubuntu, so you mileage may vary with 
the above command.  If you are using Ubuntu, you could install the 
cran2deb4ubuntu PPA which has the latest lme4.  (http://tiny.cc/c2d4u).

Michael


